address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, content_transformer(tolower)) # 
Mystopwords <- c(stopwords("english"), c("must", "will", "can"))
address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, removeWords, Mystopwords) # 
address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, removePunctuation) # 
address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, removeNumbers) #
address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, stripWhitespace) # 
address.corpus <- tm_map(address.corpus, content_transformer(trimws)) #

*** 13-2 *** tidy-text TF-IDF

us.president.address <- tidy(data_corpus_inaugural) %>% 
  filter(Year > 2000) %>% 
  group_by(President, FirstName) %>% 
  summarise_all(list(~trimws(paste(., collapse = " ")))) %>%
  arrange(Year) %>% 
  ungroup()
us.president.address
## # A tibble: 4 x 5
##   President FirstName text                                   Year   Party       
##   <chr>     <chr>     <chr>                                  <chr>  <chr>       
## 1 Bush      George W. "President Clinton, distinguished gue~ 2001 ~ Republican ~
## 2 Obama     Barack    "My fellow citizens:\n\nI stand here ~ 2009 ~ Democratic ~
## 3 Trump     Donald J. "Chief Justice Roberts, President Car~ 2017   Republican  
## 4 Biden     Joseph R. "Chief Justice Roberts, Vice Presiden~ 2021   Democratic
# tidy text
#   
address.words <- us.president.address %>% 
  unnest_tokens(output = word, input = text)
address.words
## # A tibble: 11,986 x 5
##    President FirstName Year      Party                 word         
##    <chr>     <chr>     <chr>     <chr>                 <chr>        
##  1 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican president    
##  2 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican clinton      
##  3 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican distinguished
##  4 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican guests       
##  5 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican and          
##  6 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican my           
##  7 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican fellow       
##  8 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican citizens     
##  9 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican the          
## 10 Bush      George W. 2001 2005 Republican Republican peaceful     
## # ... with 11,976 more rows
# 
address.words <- address.words %>% 
  anti_join(stop_words, by="word") %>% #
  filter(!grepl(patter = "\\d+", word)) %>%  #
  mutate(word = gsub(pattern = "'", replacement ="",word)) %>% #
  mutate(word = gsub(pattern = "america|americas|american|americans",
                     replacement = "america", word)) %>% # 
  count(President, word, sort = TRUE, name =  'count') %>% #   
  ungroup()
address.words
## # A tibble: 2,743 x 3
##    President word    count
##    <chr>     <chr>   <int>
##  1 Bush      america    50
##  2 Biden     america    38
##  3 Obama     america    34
##  4 Trump     america    34
##  5 Bush      freedom    30
##  6 Obama     nation     18
##  7 Obama     people     18
##  8 Bush      country    17
##  9 Bush      nation     17
## 10 Bush      liberty    16
## # ... with 2,733 more rows
#  
address.words %>% 
  group_by(word) %>% 
  summarise(count = sum(count)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(count)) %>% 
  top_n(n = 10, wt = count) %>% # => 10  
  ggplot(aes(reorder(word, count), count)) +
  geom_col(color = "dimgray", fill = "salmon", width = 0.6, show.legend = FALSE) +
  # theme(axis.test.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  geom_text(aes(label = count), size = 3.5, color = "black", vjust = 1) +
  labs(x = NULL, y ='Term Frequency (count)') +
  coord_flip()

# tf-idf - bind_tf_idf() 
address.words <- address.words %>% 
  bind_tf_idf(term = word, document = President, n = count)
address.words

# => tf, idf, tf_idf  
#  tf-idf  
address.words %>% 
  arrange(desc(tf_idf)) %>% 
  mutate(President = factor(President,
                            levels = c("Clinton", "Bush", "Obama", "Trump", "Biden"))) %>% 
  group_by(President) %>% 
  top_n(7, wt = tf_idf) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(reorder_within(word, tf_idf, President), tf_idf, fill = President)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~President, ncol = 2, scales = "free") +
  scale_x_reordered() +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency") +
  coord_flip()

# tf-idf  7  
address.words %>% 
  arrange(desc(tf)) %>% 
  mutate(President = factor(President,
                            levels = c("Clinton", "Bush", "Obama", "Trump", "Biden"))) %>% 
  group_by(President) %>% 
  top_n(7, wt = tf) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(reorder_within(word, tf, President), tf, fill = President)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~President, ncol = 2, scales = "free") +
  scale_x_reordered() +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Term Frequency(proportion)") +
  coord_flip()
